# LangGraph Rules

- Every multi-agent workflow uses LangGraph in `orchestrator/`.
- Each agent returns typed state via Pydantic models in `agents/*/state.py`.
- Never call another agent directly — only the supervisor routes via `orchestrator/router.py`.
- Graph definition lives in `orchestrator/graph.py`; nodes in `nodes.py`, edges in `edges.py`.
- Workflow state is immutable per node — return new state dict, do not mutate in place.
- Emit events via `orchestrator/events.py` after significant state transitions.
- Agent tools are registered in `agents/*/tools.py` and invoked through the tool layer.
